CG041268 Obsolete Issued: 1964 Added: 2011-08-14 Last Update: 2019-03-22 Color: Purple Mold: H&C (CJ) Inlay: R-White Catalog#: N1470 Contributed by: Brian "Mr. Splashbar" Cashman The Club Bingo had a single 21 game in 1967. Fuller lists 21 and slots only, I doubt they ever had roulette. I think they used their 1966 FM tokens for dollar
bets. Since they had 12 1/2 cent chips those ND chips were probably used as quarters. A blackjack would pay 37 1/2 cents. Johnny Jones had his complete collection of Morgan silver dollars displayed on the wall. Show
